        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "When you create a \"like\" constraint for select you do it somehow like this:\r\n{{$select->where('mycol LIKE ?', $where . '%');}}\r\nBut that way it's possible to \"inject\" more percent signs into the \"where\". I am not aware of any adapter method, that could be used to sanite the {{$where}} variable. The percent or question mark are obvious, but there might be other characters in other DBMSs. \r\n\r\nUse case: \r\nSearch database column for strings containing \"100% sure\". When used with syntax proposed above, it would match strings like \"100kb is enough for everyone, that's for sure\". "
        },
